description: This fascinating documentary takes viewers on a journey along Australia's Dinosaur Trail in Outback Queensland, visiting museums, dig sites and towns rich in prehistoric fossils and artifacts. It showcases rare dinosaur skeletons, footprints, ancient marine reptiles like Kronosaurus, and the world's only dinosaur stampede site at Lark Quarry. An insightful exploration of these magnificent creatures that once roamed the land.
